						<summary>

						<p>On a stone set up in front of the village <hi rend="italic">chāvaḍi.</hi></p>						

						<p>Saṁkama, 1183 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated the 4th regnal year of the king, Subhakṛit, Māgha śu. 10, Monday, the <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> corresponding to 1183 A.D., January 5. The weekday, however, was Wednesday.</p>						

						<p>It records a gift to the god Rēvaṇēśvara. It mentions the <hi rend="italic">āchārya</hi> of the temple. The epigraph is damaged.</p>						

						</summary>
